During the rework I saw sr-only bootstrap class used to hide the check-code button upon challenge completion. In my opinion this could be confusing and/or annoying for people using screen readers, therefore I have changed the logic used to toggle this button's visibility. sr-only class is needed because we want this element to be available for screen readers half a second after a challenge is completed but we don't want to be visible. If removed button is visible for half a second before it is hidden which results in an unpleasant flick.
